Chrysler Overseas Capital Corp said itauthorized redemption on April 17 of its 4-3/4 pct and five pctconvertible debentures due 1988.    The Chrysler Corp unit said the move is prompted by theparent company's three-for-two stock split, which requires arecalculation of the debentures' conversion prices that willadversely affect those prices by at least five pct.    Chrysler said holders converting debentures before thestock split becomes effective March 23 will receive a greaternumber of shares on a post-split basis than if they convertafterwards. Reuter&#3;